<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1302,1508]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1374,1400]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments:</emphasis>
See above notes. After the work of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruckes, H." box="[733,910,1374,1401]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="86 - 88" refId="ref60922" refString="Ruckes, H. (1946 b) Mecidea minor, a new species of pentatomid from New Mexico. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 41 (3), 86 - 88." type="journal article" year="1946">Ruckes (1946b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sailer, R. I." box="[963,1111,1374,1401]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="471 - 505" refId="ref61276" refString="Sailer, R. I. (1952) A review of the stink bugs of the genus Mecidea. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 102 (3309), 471 - 505. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.102 - 3309.471" type="journal article" year="1952">Sailer (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, it was believed that this species only occurred in the West Indies. 
<bibRefCitation author="Eger, J. E. Jr. &amp; Dobbs, T. T." box="[579,823,1410,1437]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref48265" refString="Eger, J. E. Jr. &amp; Dobbs, T. T. (2010) Mecidea longula Stal (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Pentatominae: Mecideini) is established in south Florida. Insecta Mundi, 109, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2010">Eger &amp; Dobbs (2010)</bibRefCitation>
first recorded 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1176,1410,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Mecidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis box="[987,1176,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mecidea longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[1348,1433,1410,1436]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Florida</collectingRegion>
. They reported numerous specimens from various collecting dates, providing strong evidence that this species is established in 
<collectingRegion box="[311,396,1482,1508]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Florida</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
